-- Former Amway Unit Quixtar Settles Lawsuit for $155 Million, Lawyers Say
-- B y   K a r e n   G u l l o
-- 2010-11-03T18:07:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/former-amway-unit-quixtar-settles-lawsuit-for-155-million-lawyers-say.html
Quixtar Inc., a former subsidiary
of Amway Corp., and the Boies, Schiller & Flexner LLP law firm
filed a settlement estimated at $155 million to resolve a
lawsuit brought by three former independent business owners,
the attorneys said in a e-mailed press release.  To contact the reporter on this story:
